Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method for acoustic modeling in speech synthesis, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech synthesis, which involves the generation of sound. 
- cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with the modeling of speech signals. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a modified attention mechanism for sequence-to-sequence modeling, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a method for improving the naturalness of synthetic speech, which involves AI techniques.
